port List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def numPairsDivisibleBy60(self, time: List[int]) -> int:\n        # Create a list to store the count of remainders\n        remainder_count = [0] * 60\n        pair_count = 0\n        \n        for t in time:\n            # Calculate the remainder of the current song duration when divided by 60\n            remainder = t % 60\n            \n            # Find the complement remainder that would make the sum divisible by 60\n            complement = (60 - remainder) % 60\n            \n            # Add the count of the complement remainder to the pair count\n            pair_count += remainder_count[complement]\n            \n            # Update the count of the current remainder\n            remainder_count[remainder] += 1\n        \n        return pair_count\n```\n\nThis solution efficiently counts the number of pairs of songs whose total duration is divisible by 60 by using a list to keep track of the remainders of each song duration when divided by 60. It then checks for each song if there is a previously seen song that, when added to the current song, results in a total duration divisible by 60.", "estimated_date": 1552780800000}